I would say take 140 in Fall 2020 or take 126 next semester instead, if you plan on using probability as a tool for inference. If you're interested in raw probability theory, then 134 is still a solid option

children.subject: It depends on what your goals are. You could probably take 189 with just 70 as your probability background, but you'll come to a point where you won't be able to develop a deeper understanding of inference until you take Prob 140 or EECS 126
Do you think it is still worth it to take cs189 and stat140 concurrently?
Is it really mandatory ee126? I heard is one one the most, if not the most, difficult eecs class and rumors says the average student in that class usually did very well in both cs70 and cs170.
